orkflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:83:                \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:141:                self._print_detail(\"result: dynamic-access report unavailable after test run\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:145:                \"Optimistic dynamic-access coverage ({covered}/{total})\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:171:        \"\"\"Run the gradle task to generate a fresh DA coverage report.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:178:            \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:185:                \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:192:            report = load_dynamic_access_coverage_report(\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:1:# Dynamic-Access Workflow Specification\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:9:The dynamic-access workflow (`workflow: dynamic_access_iterative`) generates\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:11:**dynamic-access call site** reported by the reachability repo's coverage tool\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:12:is exercised at runtime. Coverage of those call sites is required before\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:15:class until coverage is reached or the per-class budget is exhausted.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:27:| Class iteration prompt | strategy `prompts[\"dynamic-access-iteration\"]` | yes |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:28:| Keep tests without DA gain | `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` | no |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:32:- One **test class file per dynamic-access report class**, located under\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:63:- `current_report` — most recent `DynamicAccessCoverageReport` (`None` triggers\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:82:    Setup[Setup<br/>scaffold + source context + agent] --> Initial[Initial dynamic-access report]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:103:    Start([run begins]) --> Gen[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:107:    Load -- \"has dynamic access\" --> Phase2[Enter dynamic-access phase]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:115:fallback runs only when no usable dynamic-access guidance exists at the\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:149:    ReachedNT --> RegenReport[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:156:    ClassState -- \"covered_calls increased\" --> PartialCommit[Commit partial coverage<br/>advance class_checkpoint]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:173:  itself fails — coverage data is the deciding signal.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:178:### 6.3 Coverage report mid-run failure\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:180:A missing or unparsable `dynamic-access-coverage.json` after the initial\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:198:2. The dynamic-access coverage report is regenerated **after** exploration so\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:201:3. Exploration failure is non-fatal for the dynamic-access loop; it only\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:211:    Improved -- no --> Keep{keep-tests-without-dynamic-access<br/>AND tests changed since start<br/>AND prompt_iterations > 0}\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:259:The `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` flag is the only mechanism for\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:260:producing a successful run when no class achieved coverage gain. It is\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:271:| `utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py` | `load_dynamic_access_coverage_report`, `compute_class_delta`, `format_call_sites`. |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:273:| `prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md` | Per-class prompt template. |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:274:| Reachability-repo Gradle tasks | `scaffold`, `populateArtifactURLs`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `test`, `nativeTest`, `generateMetadata`, `generateLibraryStats`. |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:281:1. The dynamic-access report at the end of Phase 2 contains zero uncovered\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:284:   `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` was set and tests changed.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes native execution pass by skipping the failing native path, disabling assertions, or removing coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:91:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API or native runtime change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For native skips: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./forge/tests/test_metrics_paths.py:31:            \"code_coverage_percent\": 4.0,\n./forge/tests/test_metrics_paths.py:44:        \"stage\": \"metadata_fix_failed\",\n./forge/tests/test_metrics_paths.py:151:                                \"libraryCoverage\": {\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:11:from utility_scripts.dynamic_access_report import DynamicAccessClass, DynamicAccessCoverageReport\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:15:    def test_class_completion_progress_prints_overall_coverage(self) -> None:\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:16:        report = DynamicAccessCoverageReport(\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:35:            \"[dynamic-access] =======================