ilable types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:440:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:444:| `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.4` | `pi` | `javac_iterative` |\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:447:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:469:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:489:- Parse JaCoCo XML coverage:\n./stats/org.mortbay.jetty/servlet-api/2.5-20081211/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.mortbay.jetty/servlet-api/2.5-20081211/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.mortbay.jetty/servlet-api/2.5-20081211/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.mortbay.jetty/servlet-api/2.5-20081211/stats.json:21:    \"libraryCoverage\" : {\n./stats/org.eclipse.jetty.websocket/websocket-api/9.4.40.v20210413/execution-metrics.json:15:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.eclipse.jetty.websocket/websocket-api/9.4.40.v20210413/execution-metrics.json:19:      \"libraryCoverage\": {\n./stats/org.eclipse.jetty.websocket/websocket-api/9.4.40.v20210413/execution-metrics.json:49:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 76.41\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessReportInvocationTask.java:19: * generated JSON files under `build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access`.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessReportInvocationTask.java:49:                .resolve(\"dynamic-access\");\n./stats/org.eclipse.jetty.websocket/websocket-common/9.4.40.v20210413/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" 